        },
        {
          "title": "Rabbi Chiya's Explanation: Rabbi Splits His Vote Between Oto V'et Beno and Kissui Hadam",
          "display_title": "Rabbi's Split Vote",
          "timestamp": "32:30"
        },
        {
          "title": "Rabbi Meir's Reasoning: Using Shechutei Chutz (Korbanot Outside the Mikdash) to Show Invalid Shechita Still Counts",
          "display_title": "Rabbi Meir Reasoning",
          "timestamp": "33:40"
        },
        {
          "title": "Rabbi Shimon's Counter-Argument: The Phrase 'Asher Ye'achel' Shows Shechita Must Make Meat Edible",
          "display_title": "Shimon Counter",
          "timestamp": "38:40"
        },
        {
          "title": "Hypothetical: Does Invalid Shechita of Mother Count for Fetus in Womb (Ben Pekuah)?",
          "display_title": "Fetus in Womb",
          "timestamp": "47:51"
        },
        {
          "title": "Rabbi Meir's Limit: The Heter (Permissibility) Comes Through the Mother, Not Applied Directly to Fetus",
          "display_title": "Heter Through Mother",
          "timestamp": "53:04"
        },
        {
          "title": "Rabbi Shimon's Concession: Invalid Shechita at Least Prevents Neveilah Status, Even If Not Permitting Benefit",
          "display_title": "Neveilah Status",
